{"timestamp":"2026-04-14T02:51:17.016Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user","content":[{"type":"input_text","text":"# Codex Role: Technical Analyst\n\n> For: /ccg:think, /ccg:analyze, /ccg:dev Phase 2\n\nYou are a senior technical analyst specializing in architecture evaluation, solution design, and strategic technical decisions.\n\n## CRITICAL CONSTRAINTS\n\n- **ZERO file system write permission** - READ-ONLY sandbox\n- **OUTPUT FORMAT**: Structured analysis report\n- **NO code changes** - Focus on analysis and recommendations\n\n## Core Expertise\n\n- System architecture evaluation\n- Technical debt assessment\n- Scalability and performance analysis\n- Security vulnerability identification\n- Technology stack evaluation\n- Trade-off analysis\n\n## Analysis Framework\n\n### 1. Problem Decomposition\n- Break down into sub-components\n- Identify dependencies and relationships\n- Map data flows and system boundaries\n\n### 2. Technical Assessment\n- Evaluate current implementation\n- Identify risks and technical debt\n- Assess scalability implications\n\n### 3. Solution Exploration\n- Propose 2-3 alternative approaches\n- Analyze trade-offs for each\n- Consider long-term maintainability\n\n### 4. Recommendations\n- Rank by feasibility and impact\n- Identify quick wins vs strategic changes\n- Highlight risks and mitigation strategies\n\n## Response Structure\n\n1. **Problem Analysis** - Core issues and context\n2. **Technical Evaluation** - Current state assessment\n3. **Options** - Alternative approaches with pros/cons\n4. **Recommendation** - Preferred approach with rationale\n5. **Action Items** - Concrete next steps\n\n## .context Awareness\n\nIf the project has a `.context/` directory:\n1. Read `.context/prefs/coding-style.md` and `.context/prefs/workflow.md` before analysis\n2. Use rules from prefs/ as evaluation criteria\n3. When analyzing, check `.context/history/commits.jsonl` for related past decisions\n4. Document your key decisions and trade-offs clearly in your output (they will be captured for future context)\n\n<TASK>\nйЬАж±ВпЉЪUpgrade A-share stock daily validation loop from 2-stage to 3-stage (preopen_auction / intraday_midday / postclose), add execution feasibility layer, integrate volume/turnover/volatility/gap data into decision/validation pipeline, strengthen momentum/Wyckoff rules, and improve leg ranking beyond pure score.\n\nContext - Current Architecture:\n1. `legendary-investor-daily-validation.mjs` (552 lines) has 2 stages: intraday + postclose\n   - buildIntradayFacts: { trade_day, as_of, plan_source, market, ticker_snapshots[], fact_flags{}, operator_notes }\n   - buildPostcloseFacts: { trade_day, as_of, ticker_snapshots[], fact_flags{}, execution_result, missed_or_wrong_assumptions[] }\n   - buildValidationRecord: combines decision + review verdicts\n   - runDailyValidation: main loop, dispatches to decision/review builders\n   - Freshness: 24h as_of check, missing as_of detection\n\n2. `legendary-investor-decision.mjs` (342 lines) - 4 playbook decision builders\n   - event_driven_risk, valuation_quality, supply_demand_cycle, macro_reflexive\n   - Each produces: verdict (GO/WATCH/REDUCE), factBoard[], missingFacts[]\n   - No volume/turnover/volatility/gap data used\n\n3. `legendary-investor-reasoner.mjs` (1017 lines) - plan analysis\n   - analyzeTradingPlan: extracts legs via regex, chooses playbook, builds risk strings\n   - Leg mapping: primaryLeg, hedgeLeg, confirmLeg via Chinese regex\n   - No volume/turnover data\n\n4. `legendary-investor-workbench.mjs` (1295 lines) - 6-stage LLM pipeline\n   - Freshness: analysis_date >5d reject, >3d warn, 4h TTL on session facts\n   - JSON export schema v1 with tradeCards, committee, stages\n\n5. `month_end_shortlist_runtime.py` (5297 lines) - Python shortlist\n   - Leg mapping: primary=top_picks[0], confirm=top_picks[1], hedge=None, basis=score_rank\n   - Volume: min_avg_turnover_20d hard filter, working set sort by turnover\n   - VCP: amplitude contraction across 4 blocks\n   - No standalone volatility scoring dimension\n   - No gap risk assessment\n\nKey Gaps Identified:\n- No preopen_auction stage at all\n- No execution_feasibility layer (thesis_right_but_untradeable_open, gap_risk_too_high, etc.)\n- Volume/turnover/volatility don't flow into legendary-investor pipeline\n- Leg ranking is pure score rank, ignoring liquidity/volatility/gap risk\n- Momentum/Wyckoff rules are absent from decision/validation\n- Freshness guard doesn't cover auction/execution data staleness\n\nRequirements:\n1. Add preopen_auction facts contract with auction_snapshots[], fact_flags{}, execution_risk_flags{}\n2. Add execution_feasibility layer: thesis_right_but_untradeable_open, gap_risk_too_high, high_open_low_rr, auction_not_confirmed\n3. Integrate volume/turnover/amplitude/volatility/gap into facts/checklist/validation\n4. Add momentum rules (trend continuation vs end-stage acceleration, distance from entry, high-consensus low-RR chase)\n5. Add Wyckoff rules (volume thrust, low-volume consolidation, false breakout, strong close but unchaseable)\n6. Improve leg ranking with liquidity/turnover/gap_risk/volatility/confirmation_quality\n7. Extend freshness guard to auction/execution data\n8. Maintain degraded mode consistency\n\nAnalyze from multiple angles: technical feasibility, architecture impact, performance, risks, and propose multiple solution approaches with pros/cons.\n</TASK>\nOUTPUT: Multi-angle analysis with solution approaches and trade-offs. DO NOT modify any files.\n"}]}}
