{"timestamp":"2026-04-14T02:57:27.026Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"call_LEKJrQjexLVS1WcZTKs017Rr","output":"Exit code: 0\nWall time: 0.5 seconds\nOutput:\n---\r\nname: month-end-shortlist\r\ndescription: A-share short-horizon shortlist workflow for `йПИе†Эз∞≥йР≠оЕ†еЪО` screening. Uses a bounded Minervini / Oliver Kell style filter stack, structured catalysts, and compact trade-card outputs.\r\n---\r\n\r\n# Month-End Shortlist\r\n\r\nUse this skill when the user wants:\r\n\r\n- `йПИе†Эз∞≥йР≠оЕ†еЪО`\r\n- short-horizon A-share filtering\r\n- a narrowed shortlist instead of a single-stock deep dive\r\n- Minervini / Oliver Kell style strict screening\r\n\r\nThis skill is for shortlist construction.\r\n\r\nIt does not replace:\r\n\r\n- `news-index`\r\n- `stock_watch`\r\n- `tradingagents-decision-bridge`\r\n- filing verification\r\n\r\n## Default Boundary\r\n\r\n- A-share first\r\n- main board first\r\n- `300` only by whitelist\r\n- `688` excluded by default\r\n- `themes -> driver fit / business transmission` can drop candidates\r\n- stronger theme matches also add a bounded ranking bonus\r\n- structured catalysts only for hard pass/fail\r\n- VCP is a ranking signal, not a hard gate\r\n- `min_risk_reward_ratio = 1.5` by default\r\n- `backtest_mode = recent_shortlist_validation` only validates the current\r\n  shortlist names; it does not rebuild historical universes\r\n\r\n## Local Helper\r\n\r\n- `scripts\\run_month_end_shortlist.cmd \"<request.json>\" [--output <result.json>] [--markdown-output <report.md>]`\r\n- `scripts\\run_x_style_assisted_shortlist.cmd \"<base-request.json>\" --x-style-batch-result \"<batch-result.json>\" [--handles twikejin tuolaji2024] [--request-output <resolved-request.json>] [--output <result.json>] [--markdown-output <report.md>]`\r\n\r\n## Request Shape\r\n\r\nStart from:\r\n\r\n- `examples/month-end-shortlist-request.template.json`\r\n- `examples/month-end-shortlist-x-style-assisted.template.json`\r\n- `examples/month-end-shortlist-cross-market-x-style-assisted.template.json`\r\n\r\nBase-template note:\r\n\r\n- `examples/month-end-shortlist-request.template.json` is now a clean base\r\n  shortlist request\r\n- if you want macro-health to be attached by default, prefer\r\n  `macro-health-assisted-shortlist` or inject `macro_health_overlay`\r\n  explicitly\r\n\r\nKey fields:\r\n\r\n- `template_name`\r\n- `target_date`\r\n- `themes`\r\n- `macro_health_overlay`\r\n- `market_regime_overlay`\r\n- `sector_views`\r\n- `x_style_batch_result_path`\r\n- `x_style_selected_handles`\r\n- `x_style_overlays`\r\n- `exchange_scope`\r\n- `chinext_whitelist`\r\n- `exclude_star_board`\r\n- `filter_profile`\r\n- `strict_mode`\r\n- `working_set_limit`\r\n- `min_price`\r\n- `min_avg_turnover_20d`\r\n- `rs_threshold`\r\n- `require_structured_catalyst_within_window`\r\n- `backtest_mode`\r\n- `backtest_lookback_months`\r\n- `focus_tickers`\r\n\r\nCommon `filter_profile` values:\r\n\r\n- `month_end_minervini_kell_strict`\r\n- `month_end_generic`\r\n- `month_end_event_support_transition`\r\n  - use when a name already has valid trend / RS / event support but still\r\n    lacks VCP quality or full fundamental acceleration\r\n- `repair_rebound`\r\n  - use when the setup is a repair / rebound trade and strict Minervini trend\r\n    gating would be too restrictive\r\n- `earnings_catalyst_strict`\r\n  - use when only earnings / preview style catalysts should count as hard pass\r\n\r\n## Output Expectations\r\n\r\nReturn:\r\n\r\n- shortlist scorecard\r\n- kept / dropped lists\r\n- final top picks\r\n- scenario price map\r\n- compact trade cards\r\n- ticker-level recent shortlist validation\r\n\r\nMarkdown reports should surface the final top picks with:\r\n\r\n- executive-summary style analysis cards\r\n- summary header with rating / price / target date / system fit\r\n- optional Macro Health Card\r\n- optional PB-flow regime card\r\n- optional sector + core names overlay\r\n- optimistic / base / pessimistic ranges\r\n- scenario price table with explicit triggers\r\n- compact trade-card zones\r\n- strategy table for watch / confirm / trim / invalidation\r\n- score breakdown / strengths / risks / recent validation blocks\r\n- invalidation note\r\n- risk / reward summary\r\n- theme-fit notes when themes are active\r\n- recent shortlist validation metrics when `backtest_mode` is on\r\n- fallback gaps when `selection_mode != strict`\r\n\r\nIf strict top-pick rules leave the set empty:\r\n\r\n- keep the shortlist contract stable\r\n- emit `top_pick_selection_mode = near_strict` when the best kept candidates\r\n  are only slightly below strict\r\n- only emit `weak_fallback` when the kept set is materially weaker\r\n- still return the best kept candidates with explicit `why_not_ranked_higher`\r\n  gaps instead of an empty top-picks block\r\n\r\nRS handling:\r\n\r\n- when benchmark-relative RS is unreliable, use a smoothed cross-sectional\r\n  percentile instead of a brittle nearest-rank bucket\r\n\r\nLarge live scans:\r\n\r\n- if `universe_limit` is large, prefer setting `working_set_limit` so only the\r\n  most liquid candidates enter the history-fetch stage\r\n- when `working_set_limit = 0`, Eastmoney-backed broad scans can auto-apply a\r\n  bounded working set for large universes; always inspect the reported\r\n  `effective_working_set_limit`\r\n- if you need to inspect named stocks inside a broad scan, use `focus_tickers`\r\n  to keep them in the working set and surface them in `Focus Diagnostics`\r\n\r\nPB-flow / rotation overlay:\r\n\r\n- use `macro_health_overlay` when you already have a top-down macro-health read\r\n  from real yields, DXY, breakevens, liquidity, financial conditions, or a\r\n  macro desk summary\r\n- this layer should set risk posture, scenario language, and sector preference\r\n  before you fine-rank single names\r\n- default `integration_mode` is `advisory_only`\r\n- use `integration_mode = score_light` only when you want a very small\r\n  macro-posture adjustment to ranking; this should never replace hard filters\r\n- use `market_regime_overlay` when you already have a top-down flow read from\r\n  PB / prime-book notes, X posts, or a macro desk summary\r\n- use `sector_views` to express `industry first, then core leaders` instead of\r\n  forcing the workflow into a pure single-stock view\r\n- use `x_style_overlays` when you already ran `x-stock-picker-style` and want\r\n  to inject a learned X-user selection style as an advisory ranking layer\r\n- if you have a saved `x-stock-picker-style` batch result JSON, use\r\n  `x_style_batch_result_path` and optional `x_style_selected_handles` to load\r\n  overlay packs directly instead of copying them by hand\r\n- this overlay is advisory in v1:\r\n  - it should shape sector preference, risk posture, and commentary\r\n  - it should not override hard filters by itself\r\n  - `x_style_overlays` should do the same: they can reward basket/theme\r\n    matches, but they must not force a stock through hard filters\r\n\r\n## References\r\n\r\n- `docs/runtime/a-share-shortlist-screening-playbook.md`\r\n- `docs/runtime/macro-health-overlay-framework.md`\r\n- `docs/runtime/pb-flow-regime-overlay.md`\r\n- `docs/runtime/short-horizon-stock-templates.md`\r\n- `examples/a-share-month-end-shortlist.template.md`\r\n"}}
