 > 1.5 AND close > 20d high\n   - volume_stall: {triggered, rule, values} вАФ vol_ratio > 1.5 AND amplitude > 0.03 AND close_pos < 0.3\n   - low_volume_pullback: {triggered, rule, values} вАФ vol_ratio < 0.6 AND close near SMA20 (¬±2%)\n   - high_open_low_close: {triggered, rule, values} вАФ gap > 0.01 AND close_pos < 0.25\n   - low_open_high_close: {triggered, rule, values} вАФ gap < -0.005 AND close_pos > 0.75\n\n4. ADD new function compute_momentum_flags(metrics, candidate) returning dict with 4 flags:\n   - trend_continuation: SMA20>SMA50>SMA150, RSI 50-70, close>SMA10\n   - end_stage_acceleration: 3-day consecutive gain > 3% each OR 5-day gain > 15% AND RSI > 80\n   - too_far_from_entry: distance_from_entry > 15% (use stock_rules if available)\n   - high_consensus_chase: 5-day gain > 20% (simplified)\n\n5. ADD new function compute_wyckoff_flags(metrics, rows) returning dict with 5 flags:\n   - volume_thrust_up: vol_ratio > 2.0 AND close_pos > 0.7 AND close > prev_close\n   - low_volume_consolidation: 3-day avg vol_ratio < 0.7 AND avg amplitude < 0.02\n   - climax_reversal: vol_ratio > 2.0 AND amplitude > 0.05 AND close_pos < 0.3\n   - false_breakout: intraday high > 20d high BUT close < 20d high AND vol_ratio > 1.2\n   - strong_close_unchaseable: close_pos > 0.9 AND daily gain > 5% AND vol_ratio > 2.0\n\n6. ADD compute_execution_composite_score(metrics, tape, momentum, wyckoff) вАФ exactly as in the plan (0-100 weighted score)\n\n7. MODIFY the leg_mapping section (~line 5231) to use multi-factor ranking:\n   - For each top_pick, compute execution_composite_score\n   - Sort by composite score for primary_leg (highest composite + good liquidity + low gap)\n   - confirm_leg: highest elasticity + strong confirmation\n   - hedge_leg: pick from transition_watch if available, else None\n   - mapping_basis: \"multi_factor_rank\"\n   - Each leg entry includes: ticker, name, score, ranking_factors{liquidity_score, volatility_score, gap_risk_score, confirmation_quality, composite_rank}\n\n8. CALL compute_execution_metrics, compute_tape_signals, compute_momentum_flags, compute_wyckoff_flags in compute_candidate_snapshot() for each candidate that passes initial filters.\n\nIMPORTANT:\n- Preserve ALL existing functionality\n- New functions should be added AFTER existing helper functions but BEFORE run_month_end_shortlist\n- Use existing metrics from compute_price_metrics where possible\n- Handle None/missing data gracefully (return None for fields that can't be computed)\n- Each tape/momentum/wyckoff signal must include {triggered: bool, rule: str, values: dict}\n</TASK>\nOUTPUT: Unified Diff Patch ONLY. Strictly prohibit any actual modifications.\n","images":[],"local_images":[],"text_elements":[]}}
